Of course.
That wasn't my intention.


751
00:55:26.536 --> 00:55:28.836
I didn't feel seduced in the moment.

752
00:55:28.996 --> 00:55:31.666
So you did wonder afterwards?

753
00:55:32.706 --> 00:55:35.086
I found it atypical, nothing more.

754
00:55:35.286 --> 00:55:39.416
How did you interpret the song
Samuel Maleski played?


755
00:55:40.626 --> 00:55:42.626
I felt tension around the noise.

756
00:55:42.786 --> 00:55:47.166
Samuel Maleski imposing
his presence without showing himself.


757
00:55:47.496 --> 00:55:49.036
And Sandra's reaction...

758
00:55:49.246 --> 00:55:50.786
What was her reaction?

759
00:55:52.916 --> 00:55:54.786
She was a bit annoyed.

760
00:55:55.456 --> 00:55:58.036
And when the song started over?

761
00:55:58.666 --> 00:56:00.376
He was playing it on a loop.

762
00:56:01.666 --> 00:56:03.126
Clearly...

763
00:56:03.586 --> 00:56:04.786
good deduction.

764
00:56:04.956 --> 00:56:07.956
But how did it feel to you
in the moment?


765
00:56:08.626 --> 00:56:10.246
It added to the strangeness.

766
00:56:10.996 --> 00:56:13.496
I felt my presence was less...

767
00:56:15.026 --> 00:56:16.386
It was less relaxed.

768
00:56:16.496 --> 00:56:18.206
So you clearly felt tension.

769
00:56:18.376 --> 00:56:21.126
- You're nitpicking.
