770
00:56:21.286 --> 00:56:22.996
Did you feel tension?

771
00:56:23.166 --> 00:56:24.246
Yes.

772
00:56:25.836 --> 00:56:29.496
Did you feel that Mr. Maleski,
by playing that music,


773
00:56:30.036 --> 00:56:33.166
wanted to disrupt, or interrupt,
your interview?


774
00:56:33.406 --> 00:56:35.656
That was my first thought, yes.

775
00:56:36.706 --> 00:56:41.086
But it's hard to read the intentions
of someone you can't see.


776
00:56:41.706 --> 00:56:43.536
That's what they pay me for!

777
00:56:45.376 --> 00:56:46.666
Sandra Voyter,

778
00:56:47.166 --> 00:56:50.246
you sought a connection
to divert the interview.


779
00:56:50.476 --> 00:56:51.846
Correct?

780
00:56:51.996 --> 00:56:53.536
That's a leading question.

781
00:56:53.706 --> 00:56:55.416
There was no seduction.

782
00:56:55.746 --> 00:56:57.786
My question concerns your connection.

783
00:56:57.956 --> 00:57:02.036
In the recording you're chummy,
laughing, drinking wine.


784
00:57:02.206 --> 00:57:05.206
Were you seeking escape
from a difficult home-life


785
00:57:05.376 --> 00:57:07.456
by connecting with this young woman?

