00:57:07.626 --> 00:57:10.206
Mrs Voyter
did not initiate the meeting.


787
00:57:10.416 --> 00:57:12.376
Please answer, Mrs Voyter.

788
00:57:14.206 --> 00:57:16.536
Yes, I found her surprising.

789
00:57:16.706 --> 00:57:19.536
I hadn't seen anyone new in a while.

790
00:57:19.706 --> 00:57:21.996
And yes, I needed a drink.

791
00:57:22.166 --> 00:57:26.336
This person was intelligent and nice,
nothing more.


792
00:57:27.206 --> 00:57:31.036
That interview was hardly enough
to base a thesis on!


793
00:57:31.206 --> 00:57:35.746
She can have a laugh with a student
whose questions don't thrill her.


794
00:57:35.916 --> 00:57:38.996
Would you say the music
Mr. Maleski played


795
00:57:39.166 --> 00:57:41.166
so aggressively

796
00:57:41.336 --> 00:57:43.206
indicated he was jealous of you,

797
00:57:43.376 --> 00:57:45.536
or Miss... Mrs Solidor? Sorry.

798
00:57:45.746 --> 00:57:48.416
The music was a cover
of 50 Cent's P.I.M.P.,


799
00:57:48.586 --> 00:57:50.836
a deeply misogynistic song.

800
00:57:50.996 --> 00:57:52.786
It was an instrumental version.

801
00:57:52.956 --> 00:57:54.416
Answer, please.

802
00:57:54.626 --> 00:57:58.416
Could your husband's song choice
express his jealousy?


803
00:57:58.586 --> 00:57:59.586
I can answer.

804
00:58:01.036 --> 00:58:04.536
He often played that song.
