Would you call it impossible?

1005
01:08:45.086 --> 01:08:46.956
No, but highly improbable.

1006
01:08:47.126 --> 01:08:48.786
Meaning it is possible.

1007
01:08:49.166 --> 01:08:51.956
As it's possible
I'll be president someday.


1008
01:08:52.186 --> 01:08:53.556
I know the definition.

1009
01:08:53.706 --> 01:08:55.166
It's improbable for a reason.

1010
01:08:55.336 --> 01:08:58.496
In your hypothesis,
in order to explain the angle


1011
01:08:58.726 --> 01:09:00.136
of these 3 spatters,

1012
01:09:00.286 --> 01:09:03.666
we have to imagine
that Mr. Maleski's head


1013
01:09:03.836 --> 01:09:07.376
was leaning way out,
around 80 cm past the guardrail.


1014
01:09:07.536 --> 01:09:10.496
This implies the aggressor forced him

1015
01:09:10.706 --> 01:09:12.706
to lean backwards over the void,

1016
01:09:13.286 --> 01:09:15.746
shoving him against the guardrail,

1017
01:09:15.916 --> 01:09:18.916
his entire torso pitched backwards.

1018
01:09:19.246 --> 01:09:23.586
The aggressor would have
to be leaning very far out


1019
01:09:23.786 --> 01:09:26.166
while holding a heavy object

1020
01:09:26.336 --> 01:09:29.496
and striking the victim
with powerful momentum.


1021
01:09:29.666 --> 01:09:30.956
All these elements,

1022
01:09:31.126 --> 01:09:33.996
in addition to
the defendant's body mass,


1023
01:09:34.166 --> 01:09:36.336
make this hypothesis highly improbable.

1024
01:09:36.496 --> 01:09:37.666
But not impossible.

1025
01:09:42.086 --> 01:09:45.206
Listen Daniel,
I asked to see you because...


1026
01:09:45.376 --> 01:09:48.626
I know you have a vested interest
in this case.


1027
01:09:48.786 --> 01:09:51.496
I've allowed you
to attend the trial so far.


1028
01:09:51.666 --> 01:09:53.036
But tomorrow will be

1029
01:09:53.266 --> 01:09:55.056
far more complicated.

1030
01:09:55.206 --> 01:09:57.996
We'll be covering
some disturbing details,


1031
01:09:58.166 --> 01:10:00.666
so I've decided
you won't be attending.


1032
01:10:01.786 --> 01:10:03.456
I think I can hear anything.

1033
01:10:03.626 --> 01:10:04.456
What?

1034
01:10:04.626 --> 01:10:06.586
I think I can hear anything.

1035
01:10:06.996 --> 01:10:08.786
- Yeah?
- I'm prepared.


1036
01:10:08.956 --> 01:10:12.036
You can hear it,
but can you handle it?


1037
01:10:12.206 --> 01:10:13.786
We have a job to do.

1038
01:10:13.956 --> 01:10:17.536
We need to be able to work...
with serenity.


1039
01:10:17.706 --> 01:10:19.336
I've never disrupted the trial.

1040
01:10:19.496 --> 01:10:20.996
Disrupted...

1041
01:10:21.336 --> 01:10:23.036
That's not the point.

1042
01:10:24.376 --> 01:10:27.666
We need to be able
to evoke the facts bluntly.


1043
01:10:28.916 --> 01:10:30.996
We have to address everything,

1044
01:10:31.166 --> 01:10:33.536
without fear of hurting you.

1045
01:10:36.246 --> 01:10:37.996
I've already been hurt.

1046
01:10:39.706 --> 01:10:41.916
And that's why I need...

1047
01:10:43.286 --> 01:10:45.456
to hear, so I can get past it.

1048
01:10:45.626 --> 01:10:47.746
The trial is not about you hearing.

1049
01:10:47.916 --> 01:10:50.286
It's about establishing the truth,

1050
01:10:50.456 --> 01:10:53.206
without being forced
to censor ourselves.


1051
01:10:53.666 --> 01:10:56.166
When has anyone
censored themselves?


1052
01:10:57.356 --> 01:11:00.016
Even if you forbid me to come,

1053
01:11:00.416 --> 01:11:02.956
I'll find out.
I'll know what happened


1054
01:11:03.126 --> 01:11:04.956
from TV, radio, internet.

1055
01:11:05.836 --> 01:11:07.456
I'll be obsessed.

1056
01:11:19.536 --> 01:11:21.376
Mrs Voyter, you claim

1057
01:11:21.586 --> 01:11:24.916
your husband attempted suicide

1058
01:11:25.286 --> 01:11:28.456
You remembered late,
which is quite surprising.


1059
01:11:28.626 --> 01:11:31.586
Can you describe
the episode in detail?


1060
01:11:31.746 --> 01:11:32.916
Yes.

1061
01:11:38.746 --> 01:11:43.246
It happened a few weeks
after he stopped his medication.


1062
01:11:44.376 --> 01:11:46.876
I found him lying on the floor...

1063
01:11:47.916 --> 01:11:50.246
early in the morning, in his room.

1064
01:11:51.996 --> 01:11:53.166
He'd...

1065
01:11:53.536 --> 01:11:55.286
had a lot to drink..

1066
01:11:56.036 --> 01:11:58.746
The night before, and passed out.

1067
01:12:00.336 --> 01:12:03.746
He'd vomited,
and in the vomit, I saw aspirin.


1068
01:12:04.626 --> 01:12:07.996
The pills had nearly dissolved.

1069
01:12:10.086 --> 01:12:12.876
At first I didn't understand
what it was.


1070
01:12:13.626 --> 01:12:16.086
But later, I found...

1071
01:12:16.786 --> 01:12:19.586
empty blister packs
in the kitchen garbage.


1072
01:12:20.706 --> 01:12:23.336
I cleaned it all up
and put him in bed.


1073
01:12:23.916 --> 01:12:25.166
Later,

1074
01:12:25.336 --> 01:12:26.956
when he felt better,

1075
01:12:27.166 --> 01:12:29.086
he didn't want to discuss it.

1076
01:12:29.246 --> 01:12:32.036
He just said he'd
stopped his meds too soon.


1077
01:12:33.706 --> 01:12:35.666
You had separate bedrooms?

1078
01:12:36.666 --> 01:12:40.086
It was his office,
and he usually slept there, yes.


1079
01:12:41.746 --> 01:12:46.036
I see. What made you
go into his room so early?


1080
01:12:46.206 --> 01:12:48.746
I wake up very early.
He did too, sometimes.


1081
01:12:48.916 --> 01:12:52.166
We occasionally spent that time
together, talking.


1082
01:12:52.336 --> 01:12:53.746
At 6 in the morning?

1083
01:12:53.916 --> 01:12:56.376
Yes, if I saw the light on. Yes.

1084
01:12:57.166 --> 01:13:00.246
We'd stopped sharing a bed,
but we were very close.


1085
01:13:00.416 --> 01:13:02.246
I would often...

1086
01:13:03.336 --> 01:13:06.336
finish the night with him,
in the office bed.


1087
01:13:07.836 --> 01:13:09.746
I'd gone down to make coffee.

1088
01:13:09.916 --> 01:13:12.916
I saw his door was ajar, and...

1089
01:13:13.456 --> 01:13:15.496
I saw him lying on the floor.

1090
01:13:15.916 --> 01:13:18.086
No one else witnessed that?

1091
01:13:18.206 --> 01:13:19.206
No.

1092
01:13:19.536 --> 01:13:21.956
Thank you, you may sit down.

1093
01:13:24.246 --> 01:13:25.626
Did you know that?

1094
01:13:27.416 --> 01:13:29.166
Which antidepressant
did you prescribe?


1095
01:13:29.336 --> 01:13:31.086
Escitalopram, 20 mg per day.

1096
01:13:31.286 --> 01:13:33.336
- Was it his choice to stop?
- Yes.


1097
01:13:33.746 --> 01:13:36.956
About 7 months before he died
he wanted to wean off.


1098
01:13:37.126 --> 01:13:40.916
I recommended a tapering plan
with weekly check-ins.


1099
01:13:41.086 --> 01:13:42.586
Any suicidal ideation?

1100
01:13:43.336 --> 01:13:45.246
No, Samuel wasn't depressive.

1101
01:13:45.416 --> 01:13:48.586
I'd prescribed Escitalopram
as an emotional shield


1102
01:13:49.416 --> 01:13:52.126
to help him cope
after his son's accident.


1103
01:13:52.286 --> 01:13:56.746
Can sudden withdrawal from a low dose
trigger a suicide attempt?


1104
01:13:57.606 --> 01:13:59.856
Anything's possible in theory,

1105
01:13:59.996 --> 01:14:04.246
but why would he have asked me
to help him wean off,


1106
01:14:04.416 --> 01:14:07.336
then stop behind my back?
Makes no sense.


1107
01:14:07.496 --> 01:14:10.336
And no mention of it
in our weekly sessions?


1108
01:14:23.416 --> 01:14:26.626
Have you ever had a patient
commit suicide,


1109
01:14:26.856 --> 01:14:28.476
or attempt suicide?

1110
01:14:28.626 --> 01:14:30.876
In French, "committing suicide"

1111
01:14:31.036 --> 01:14:34.666
means both trying and succeeding.

1112
01:14:34.896 --> 01:14:35.896
It's the action.

1113
01:14:36.036 --> 01:14:37.706
Thanks for the language lesson.

1114
01:14:38.186 --> 01:14:39.636
No patient has committed suicide.

1115
01:14:39.786 --> 01:14:42.126
Aside from Mr. Maleski,

1116
01:14:42.286 --> 01:14:44.836
since we're here
to rule on the question.


1117
01:14:44.996 --> 01:14:46.286
In any case,

1118
01:14:46.456 --> 01:14:49.246
we can't consider you
an expert on suicide,


1119
01:14:49.416 --> 01:14:50.586
failed or successful.

1120
01:14:51.336 --> 01:14:54.746
You said your husband
refused to discuss it with you,


1121
01:14:54.916 --> 01:14:56.666
or anyone else, apparently.

1122
01:14:56.836 --> 01:14:58.126
Why, do you think?

1123
01:15:00.586 --> 01:15:02.166
Because he was ashamed.

1124
01:15:02.336 --> 01:15:04.586
He had a lot of...

1125
01:15:09.286 --> 01:15:11.536
It's too complicated.
Can I change the language, please?


1126
01:15:13.126 --> 01:15:14.376
Thanks.

1127
01:15:16.286 --> 01:15:18.376
Yeah, I think because he was ashamed.

1128
01:15:19.566 --> 01:15:22.606
Samuel had
a lot of issues with shame.


1129
01:15:22.806 --> 01:15:24.136
It's complicated.

1130
01:15:27.246 --> 01:15:31.246
He was frustrated with teaching.
It had become a burden,


1131
01:15:31.956 --> 01:15:33.626
and he wanted to write.

1132
01:15:34.416 --> 01:15:36.536
He'd been working
on a novel for years,


1133
01:15:36.706 --> 01:15:38.836
before and after Daniel's accident.

1134
01:15:40.456 --> 01:15:41.746
I read everything he wrote.

1135
01:15:41.916 --> 01:15:44.206
I thought it was really good
and I told him so.


1136
01:15:44.666 --> 01:15:46.626
But from one day to another,
he just...


1137
01:15:47.166 --> 01:15:49.786
couldn't do it anymore,
he just stopped.


1138
01:15:51.286 --> 01:15:53.376
It made him feel like a coward.

1139
01:15:54.166 --> 01:15:56.286
He would belittle himself.

1140
01:15:57.706 --> 01:16:00.496
He ended up convincing himself
he could not write


1141
01:16:00.666 --> 01:16:03.666
because of his dependency
on the medication.


1142
01:16:03.836 --> 01:16:05.666
He wanted to free himself of that,

1143
01:16:05.836 --> 01:16:08.126
and he could not, of course not...

1144
01:16:08.286 --> 01:16:09.916
I'm sorry, I'm not finished.

1145
01:16:10.086 --> 01:16:12.726
He could not talk about
the suicide attempt


1146
01:16:12.836 --> 01:16:16.286
because his feelings of failure
were just too painful.


1147
01:16:16.456 --> 01:16:18.166
He never spoke of that.

1148
01:16:18.336 --> 01:16:19.336
Not once.

1149
01:16:19.376 --> 01:16:23.166
He blamed you for getting him hooked
on the pills from the first session.


1150
01:16:23.336 --> 01:16:24.456
It drove him mad.

1151
01:16:24.666 --> 01:16:26.166
He and I decided together.

1152
01:16:26.336 --> 01:16:29.836
You can't deny you're at the center
of this equation.


1153
01:16:30.246 --> 01:16:33.666
Samuel came to see me
because he felt guilty,


1154
01:16:33.836 --> 01:16:36.496
but mostly because you blamed him.

1155
01:16:36.666 --> 01:16:39.086
He described your behavior

1156
01:16:39.246 --> 01:16:41.336
as quite castrating.

1157
01:16:41.746 --> 01:16:43.706
You made him pay

1158
01:16:44.036 --> 01:16:45.786
for the accident

1159
01:16:45.996 --> 01:16:49.416
by forcing him to give up
what mattered most to him:


1160
01:16:49.586 --> 01:16:50.626
Writing.

1161
01:16:51.456 --> 01:16:54.876
You put him on
an emotional roller coaster.


1162
01:16:55.086 --> 01:16:57.246
On the one hand, it's true,

1163
01:16:57.416 --> 01:17:00.336
you encouraged him to write,
wanted him to succeed.


1164
01:17:00.496 --> 01:17:03.916
But if he had,
it would've been unbearable for you.


1165
01:17:04.086 --> 01:17:06.916
That's the problem.
It may have been subconscious.


1166
01:17:08.086 --> 01:17:11.416
All the material
and psychological burdens


1167
01:17:11.586 --> 01:17:14.126
resulting from the accident
were his to bear.


1168
01:17:14.286 --> 01:17:17.206
It's as though you said,
"This is your problem."


1169
01:17:17.376 --> 01:17:19.376
"You're responsible. 
Deal with it."

1170
01:17:19.536 --> 01:17:22.376
"I want to free myself from that,
to write."


1171
01:17:22.536 --> 01:17:24.126
Material burdens

1172
01:17:24.286 --> 01:17:27.416
were managed by Mrs Voyter
as much as her husband.


1173
01:17:27.586 --> 01:17:30.996
We have their bank statements,
receipts, etc.


1174
01:17:31.206 --> 01:17:33.836
I'm also talking about
the emotional load.


1175
01:17:33.996 --> 01:17:36.706
Responsibilities, sense of purpose,

1176
01:17:37.376 --> 01:17:38.586
anxiety.

1177
01:17:38.746 --> 01:17:43.166
In those areas,
Samuel felt an unbearable imbalance.


1178
01:17:43.336 --> 01:17:45.706
So what your patients
tell you is the truth?


1179
01:17:45.876 --> 01:17:47.996
As a psychoanalyst,

1180
01:17:48.166 --> 01:17:50.876
you never wondered
whether Samuel Maleski


1181
01:17:51.036 --> 01:17:54.746
might've needed to imagine
an unbearable imbalance


1182
01:17:54.916 --> 01:17:56.916
to prevent himself from writing?

1183
01:17:57.086 --> 01:18:01.086
After a while, I can tell
what's real and what isn't.


1184
01:18:01.286 --> 01:18:02.496
Lucky you.

1185
01:18:02.666 --> 01:18:04.416
I'm sorry to interrupt.

1186
01:18:04.836 --> 01:18:06.126
But...

1187
01:18:06.496 --> 01:18:08.916
I don't know. You come here,

1188
01:18:09.086 --> 01:18:12.536
OK, with maybe your opinion,
and you tell me


1189
01:18:13.626 --> 01:18:17.456
who Samuel was
and what we were going through.


1190
01:18:18.126 --> 01:18:21.456
But what you say is just

1191
01:18:22.036 --> 01:18:25.036
a little part of the whole situation.

1192
01:18:25.586 --> 01:18:26.706
You know.

1193
01:18:27.286 --> 01:18:28.666
I mean, sometimes,

1194
01:18:29.336 --> 01:18:30.706
sometimes a couple...

1195
01:18:32.286 --> 01:18:34.126
is kind of a chaos

1196
01:18:34.286 --> 01:18:36.286
and everybody is lost.

1197
01:18:36.456 --> 01:18:39.246
Sometimes we fight together
and sometimes we fight alone,


1198
01:18:39.416 --> 01:18:42.666
and sometimes we fight against
each other, that happens.


1199
01:18:42.836 --> 01:18:45.836
And I think it's possible that Samuel

1200
01:18:46.166 --> 01:18:49.876
needed to see things
the way you describe them, but...


1201
01:18:51.416 --> 01:18:53.416
If I'd been seeing a therapist,

1202
01:18:53.586 --> 01:18:57.666
he could stand here too and say
very ugly things about Samuel.


1203
01:18:57.836 --> 01:18:59.836
But would those things be true?

1204
01:19:08.496 --> 01:19:12.746
Did you resent your husband
after your son's accident?


1205
01:19:16.286 --> 01:19:18.496
We were both dealing with

1206
01:19:18.666 --> 01:19:21.786
very different emotions at that time.

1207
01:19:23.126 --> 01:19:24.706
Yes or no?

1208
01:19:27.456 --> 01:19:29.036
Yes, for a few days.

1209
01:19:29.536 --> 01:19:31.416
Daniel was on his watch.

1210
01:19:32.586 --> 01:19:35.456
Your son practically lost his sight,

1211
01:19:35.836 --> 01:19:38.286
and you only resented him
for a few days?


1212
01:19:39.416 --> 01:19:42.786
Yes, about his responsibility
for the accident. Yes.


1213
01:19:43.706 --> 01:19:44.876
Of course.

1214
01:19:45.916 --> 01:19:50.996
I mean, maybe. The doctor earlier said
something about a tragic situation.


1215
01:19:51.416 --> 01:19:54.416
I immediately refused
to see it that way.


1216
01:19:54.786 --> 01:19:57.456
I never saw Daniel as handicapped.

1217
01:19:58.286 --> 01:20:01.626
You know, I wanted to protect
him from that perception.


1218
01:20:01.786 --> 01:20:05.456
Because, as soon as you mark a child
that way, you condemn him to now


1219
01:20:05.626 --> 01:20:08.376
to not see his life as his own,

1220
01:20:08.536 --> 01:20:11.246
whereas he should feel
that it's his best life


1221
01:20:11.416 --> 01:20:13.036
because it's the only life he's got,

1222
01:20:13.206 --> 01:20:14.536
it is his own.

1223
01:20:16.836 --> 01:20:18.206
He reads books,

1224
01:20:19.286 --> 01:20:21.746
he goes on social media
like any other kid


1225
01:20:21.916 --> 01:20:23.286
he plays the piano,

1226
01:20:23.456 --> 01:20:25.376
he dreams, he cries, he laughs.

1227
01:20:25.536 --> 01:20:27.536
He's a very lively kid.

1228
01:20:27.876 --> 01:20:29.086
He's OK.

1229
01:20:30.166 --> 01:20:31.336
Yeah.

1230
01:20:33.456 --> 01:20:35.746
So perhaps, I...

1231
01:20:37.376 --> 01:20:41.536
I resented Samuel for projecting
his own pain onto Daniel, yes.


1232
01:20:44.496 --> 01:20:45.496
Thank you.

1233
01:21:06.246 --> 01:21:08.376
I want to drink all night.

1234
01:21:09.706 --> 01:21:10.876
Yeah, same.

1235
01:21:11.706 --> 01:21:12.996
I will drink.

1236
01:21:13.746 --> 01:21:14.876
To forget.

1237
01:21:15.086 --> 01:21:17.166
Come on. You're the only lawyer...

1238
01:21:19.706 --> 01:21:20.956
OK, once again.

1239
01:21:21.126 --> 01:21:23.666
No, you're really
the only lawyer I know.


1240
01:21:25.126 --> 01:21:28.626
Is it a great reason for putting
your life in someone's hands?


1241
01:21:29.036 --> 01:21:30.916
- Is it?
- No, but you're good too.


1242
01:21:31.496 --> 01:21:33.086
Right? You're good.

1243
01:21:33.246 --> 01:21:34.706
- I don't know.
- Oh, come on.


1244
01:21:36.706 --> 01:21:38.206
You look like a dog.

1245
01:21:39.496 --> 01:21:40.666
Excuse me?

1246
01:21:40.836 --> 01:21:42.586
No, a beautiful dog.

1247
01:21:43.586 --> 01:21:44.916
How do you say it?

1248
01:21:45.956 --> 01:21:47.536
A basset?

1249
01:21:47.706 --> 01:21:49.836
Funny you say that.
I can't trust someone


1250
01:21:50.036 --> 01:21:52.416
if I can't put
an animal's head on them.


1251
01:21:52.626 --> 01:21:54.786
Really? So what am I?

1252
01:21:57.626 --> 01:21:59.086
I'm not sure yet.

1253
01:22:02.626 --> 01:22:04.036
After all this time,

1254
01:22:04.876 --> 01:22:06.376
you still don't know?

1255
01:22:08.786 --> 01:22:10.126
OK.

1256
01:22:21.746 --> 01:22:25.706
Do you remember me from before,
